I was just able to reproduce it on `stable 2.10.0`.

As the initial bug report says, it's reproducible on a physical device but not in the simulator.

I've also noticed that the keyboard pops up when you drag back the page by just a minimum amount, in other words, it triggers with [`didStartUserGesture`](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/widgets/NavigatorState/didStartUserGesture.html).

With that in mind, I've found a hacky way to get around it by defining a `NavigatorObserver` like so

```dart
class MyNavObserver extends NavigatorObserver {
  // make a set of all the routes that actually require a keyboard
  static const Set<String> _routesWithKeyboard = {
    'search', // for example
  };

  @override
  void didStartUserGesture(Route<dynamic> route, Route<dynamic>? previousRoute) {
    // get the previous route's name
    final String? previousRouteName = previousRoute?.settings.name;

    // check if the previous route actually requires a keyboard
    if (previousRouteName != null && !_routesWithKeyboard.contains(previousRouteName)) {
      // if it doesn't require a keyboard then hide it
      FocusManager.instance.primaryFocus?.unfocus();
    }

    // call the parent function
    super.didStartUserGesture(route, previousRoute);
  }
}
```

And then simply use that on my `MaterialApp`.

