Try replacing the `TextField` in your example with `MyTextField`:

```dart
class MyTextField extends StatelessWidget {
  MyTextField({Key? key}) : super(key: key);

  final _textEditingController = TextEditingController();

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    _textEditingController.text = 'Multiline\ntext\ninput';
    _textEditingController.selection =
        TextSelection.collapsed(offset: _textEditingController.text.length);
    return TextField(
      controller: _textEditingController,
      autofocus: true,
    );
}
```

The `autofocus: true` part is important, so that the caret is already in the text field when you interact with the contents. Do not click on the Android emulator window, just give the window focus by clicking on the titlebar, or use Alt+Tab to focus the emulator. Clicking on the text field seems to correctly set the caret position to the end of the visible text, which eliminates the problem.

Then, to reproduce the issue, hit the Left arrow key one or more times. This tries to move the cursor position, which is off the visible screen, and gives the error shown in the original bug report.

